      • closePanel

        public boolean closePanel(boolean mustClose)
        This method is used to close this panel, removing as a tab from the UI. The argument will tell the panel whether it needs to close regardless of what the user wants and the result of the method should tell the caller whether the panel really was closed. (Obviously, if the panel was told that it must close, the result will be ignored.)
        Specified by:
        closePanel in class com.itko.lisa.gui.LisaGuiPanel
        Parameters:
        mustClose - a flag indicating that the panel must close regardless of any decision the user must make (typically relating to saving any pending changes).
        Returns:
        true if the panel was closed or false if not.
        See Also:
        LisaGuiPanel.destroy()
